description:
Check out this new extended gameplay demo reveal from Lord of Mysteries, a new game developed in Unreal Engine 5. This work in progress footage provided by Spark Nexa has been edited by us. You can explore in this demo the city where the story begins called Tingen. The new game based on the hit web novel Lord of the Mysteries è¯¡ç§˜ä¹‹ä¸» is an ambitious European-style ancient occult open world MMO RPG. The game blends Bloodborne's Lovecraftian Victorian steampunk aesthetic with Genshin Impact's open world exploration. It also mirrors Final Fantasy XIV's social depth through its academy and ritualistic roleplaying mechanics.

*_Description:_*

Lord of the Mysteries immerses you in a place where the line between the mundane and the supernatural is dangerously thin. Unravel secrets, harness the power of the Acting Method, and master multiple pathways to survive in a world where sanity is your most precious asset. The game faithfully adapts key moments from the original web novel, while expanding its universe with new side stories that explore the lives of ordinary characters. 

*_Gameplay Features:_*

- Exploration: Explore iconic locations like Saint Selena Cathedral, uncover secrets beyond the Chanis Gate, and face off against Blackthorn Security. Join the Divination Club, fight with the Nighthawks, and unravel the worldâ€™s mysteries.

- Darkness and Sanity: As you delve into its shadowy corners, the line between sanity and madness will blur. In this unsettling world, your sanity is your greatest asset. Remember who you are, or risk succumbing to the darkness that lurks within.

- Acting Method: Harness power to embrace the roles of different personas, immersing yourself in their traits, and master their powers to progress through the pathways. Your ability to adapt and evolve will be key to surviving the unknown and uncovering the truth behind the mysteries.

- Co-op: Tackle the toughest challenges and unravel the worldâ€™s mysteries with team-play components.

*_Release Date and Platforms:_* It is designed as a cross-platform title for PC and Mobile. There's currently no release date but the first closed beta is coming soon to China.

Written by Sefton Hill, Ian Ball, and Martin Lancaster, Arkham Knight is inspired by the long-running comic book mythos. Check out this new exclusive preview demo featuring the very first mission from the upcoming Styx: Blades of Greed, developed in Unreal Engine 5. We captured this early gameplay footage in RTX 5090 and 4K monitor (no commentary). This new stealth-driven adventure is built around infiltration, vertical level design, and careful planning. Its focus on freedom and creativity in how objectives are approached, combined with an emphasis on observation and positioning, places it alongside modern stealth-focused adventures such as Thief, Metal Gear Solid, Hitman, Dishonored, Assassinâ€™s Creed, 007 First Light and dark fantasy games franchises like Lord of the Rings.

*_Description:_*

Styx: Blades of Greed is the next entry in the Styx series, a stealth-action adventure starring the sharp-tongued goblin Styx. No longer working for others, Styx leads his own crew from a zeppelin as he hunts for Quartz, a mysterious and extremely valuable resource in a world on the verge of conflict between elves, humans, and orcs. The game builds on the foundations of the franchise while expanding player freedom and creative problem-solving.

*_Demo Features:_*

- This demo gives you access to the very beginning of the game.

- The infiltration inside a massive golem attacking Styx to destroy it from the inside, a perfect introduction and tutorial to some Styx's new tricks.

- Styx's first real mission, a high-risk zeppelin theft under the ever-watchful eye of the Inquisition in the first open environment of the game, The Wall.

- Itâ€™s a focused taste of the tone, systems, and level of freedom we're building into the full experience, just enough to get you into trouble, and hopefully out of it.

*_Gameplay Features:_*

- Three large, open environments to explore and infiltrate in your own way. You'll discover brand new areas of The Wall as you unlock your new tools. You'll be sneaking through the vile orc nest of Turquoise Dawn and the rotting Ruins of Akenash.

- Movement tools to unlock new routes and unreachable areas, such as the grappling hook and glider.

- Unlock more upgrades for your tools and powers.

- New Quartz powers, including mind control and time shifting.

- New enemy factions with their own gameplay specificities, including Inquisitors, Orcs, or Elves.

- Fresh infiltration challenges, a full liberty to design your own approaches, and situations to outsmart with Styxâ€™s trademark creativity.

description:

Brawl Stars Playlist - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGtZwVE-T07vYODoUzNweS6upEexk3024

GAME DESCRIPTION

Brawl Stars - Free

Download on iOS - https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/brawl-stars/id1229016807
Download on Android - https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.supercell.brawlstars

Fast-paced multiplayer battles from the makers of Clash of Clans, Clash Royale and Boom Beach.

Battle with friends or solo across a variety of game modes in under three minutes. Unlock and upgrade dozens of Brawlers with powerful super abilities. Purchase and collect unique skins to stand out and show off in the arena. Join or start a band to share tactics and fight together.

BATTLE IN MULTIPLE GAME MODES
- Gem Grab (3v3): Team up and out-strategize the opposing team. Collect and hold 10 gems to win, but get fragged and lose your gems.
- Showdown (Solo/Duo): A battle royale style fight for survival. Collect power ups for your Brawler. Grab a friend or play solo - be the last Brawler standing in the rowdiest battle royale yet. Winner take all!
- Bounty (3v3): Take out opponents to earn stars, but donâ€™t let them pick you off. The squad with the most stars wins the match!
- Heist (3v3): Protect your teamâ€™s safe and try to crack open your opponentsâ€™. Navigate the map to sneak, blast and blow your way clear to the enemies treasure.
- Brawl Ball (3v3): It's a whole new Brawl game! Show off your soccer/football skills and score two goals before the other team. There are no red cards here.
- Special Events: Limited time special PvE and PvP game modes.

UNLOCK AND UPGRADE BRAWLERS
Collect and upgrade a variety of Brawlers with punishing SUPER abilities, level them up with power points, and collect unique skins.

BECOME THE STAR PLAYER
Climb the local and regional leaderboards to prove youâ€™re the greatest Brawler of them all!

CONSTANTLY EVOLVING
Look out for new Brawlers, skins, maps, special events and games modes in the future.

PLEASE NOTE! Brawl Stars is free to download and play, however, some game items can also be purchased for real money. If you don't want to use this feature, please disable in-app purchases in your device's settings. Also, under our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy, you must be at least 13 years of age to play or download Brawl Stars.

Features:
- Team up for real-time 3v3 battles against players from across the world
- A fast-paced multiplayer battle royale mode made for mobile
- Unlock and collect new, powerful Brawlers - each with a signature attack and SUPER ability
- New events and game modes daily
- Battle solo or co-op
- Climb to the top of the leaderboards in global and local rankings 
- Join or start your own Club with fellow players to share tips and battle together
- Customize Brawlers with unlockable skins
- Player-designed maps offer challenging new terrain to master

Check out the latest gameplay footage from Resident Evil Requiem, presented during the most recent Resident Evil Showcase and edited by us. The new work in progress footage offers a clearer look at the gameâ€™s core design pillars, including its dual-protagonist approach, expanded gameplay mechanics, narrative direction, and difficulty settings, underlining Requiemâ€™s intent to merge intense action with deliberate, high-tension survival horror.

*_Dual Protagonists_* 

The game stars FBI analyst Grace Ashcroft and veteran DSO agent Leon S. Kennedy, each with a distinct playstyle. Players can freely switch between first-person and third-person views, allowing encounters to shift smoothly between claustrophobic horror and cinematic action.

*_Leon Kennedy_* 

Combat and Action: Leonâ€™s gameplay focuses on aggressive, skill-based combat, combining firearms, close-quarters techniques, parries, and finishing moves. New mechanics, such as wielding a hatchet or using enemy weapons like chainsaws, reinforce a more action-driven approach to survival.

*_Grace Ashcroft_* 

Survival Horror Focus: Graceâ€™s campaign emphasizes classic survival horror, with scarce resources, limited inventory space, and constant risk assessment in a zombie-infested sanatorium. Crafting items with infected blood and managing the powerful but ammo-limited Requiem assault revolver are key to survival.

*_Story and Enemies_* 

Zombies retain unsettling behaviors from their former lives, creating opportunities for strategic avoidance rather than direct confrontation. The narrative centers on â€œElpis,â€ linking Graceâ€™s past, her motherâ€™s death, and Leonâ€™s investigation.

*_Difficulty Options_* 

Multiple difficulty modes are available, including a Classic option that reintroduces Ink Ribbon saves for Grace, reinforcing tension and long-term survival planning.

*_Release Date and Platforms:_* Coming February 27, 2025, for PlayStation 5, Xbox Series consoles, Switch 2, PC, and GeForce Now.

description:
âš ï¸ *_Footage recorded by ENFANT TERRIBLE. Unauthorized use and/or duplication of this video is strictly prohibited._*

Check out the new exclusive preview demo look from the upcoming The Occultist running in Unreal Engine 5. We captured this early gameplay footage in RTX 5090 and 4K monitor (no commentary). The Occultist is a first person psychological survival horror and narrative thriller that can be best compared to a blend of The Medium's supernatural interaction and Amnesiaâ€™s vulnerability. This game is much closer to Silent Hill due to its deep focus on psychological dread, occult rituals, and atmospheric storytelling.

*_Description:_*

You play as Alan Rebels (voiced by Doug Cockle, the iconic voice actor world-renowned for his role as Geralt of Rivia in The Witcher series), a professional paranormal investigator who travels to the mysterious and abandoned island of Godstone. His mission is to uncover the truth behind the sudden disappearance of his father, who was born on the island and spoke of it often. Godstone was once home to a macabre cult that performed disturbing experiments and rituals until 1950, leaving the island cursed and populated by restless, ominous spirits.

*_Gameplay Features:_*

- The Mystic Pendulum: This is Alanâ€™s most vital tool. It features five unique mechanics that allow players to interact with the environment, manipulate objects, and communicate with the spirits of the island.

- Stealth and Investigation: Alan is not a fighter. The game focuses on "Hide and Sneak" mechanics where you must avoid direct combat with terrifying entities. Success depends on your ability to solve occult puzzles and stay out of sight.

- Atmospheric Exploration: The game emphasizes a "next-gen" visual experience, using high-quality graphics to create a claustrophobic and chilling atmosphere in the foggy streets and ruins of Godstone.

- Psychological Horror: Rather than just jump scares, the game focuses on a deep, personal narrative that challenges Alanâ€™s own convictions about the supernatural.

*_Release Date and Platforms:_* Coming in 2026 to PS5, Xbox and PC.

People LOVE These Video Game Franchises! (But I Just Don't, That's OK)
description:
We all have them. Those "Sacred Cows" of the gaming world. The franchises that get 10/10 scores, sell millions of copies, and have die-hard fanbasesâ€¦ but when you pick up the controller, you just feelâ€¦ nothing.

In this video, I am sharing my "Unpopular Gaming Opinions." These are the massive AAA franchises and cult classics that everyone else seems to adore, but I just cannot get into. To be clear: I am not saying these are bad games. I respect the developers, I respect the history, and I respect your love for them. They just aren't for me. So let's take a look at popular video game franchises that people love, but I just don't. But it's ok, just because I don't love them doesn't mean I think you're wrong if you do. 

Letâ€™s break down the list of gaming legends that I respectfully decline.

ğŸš« The Ground Rules (No RPGs)
First, a quick disclaimer. You won't see Final Fantasy, Dragon Quest, or Persona on this list. Why? Because I just don't like the RPG genre as a whole. It wouldn't be fair to critique them when the core mechanics of role-playing games don't appeal to me. We are strictly talking about genres I usually enjoy, but specific titles I don't.

ğŸï¸ Forza vs. Gran Turismo
I know Xbox fans love the Forza series (both Motorsport and Horizon), and I appreciate the car lists and the effort Turn 10 puts into them. But I am a Gran Turismo guy through and through.

The History: Maybe itâ€™s because I started with GT on the PlayStation, but that handling model is burned into my brain.

The Feel: To me, the physics in Forza just don't feel as tight. The graphics, while technically impressive, don't have the same style as Polyphony Digitalâ€™s work.

The Vibe: Even down to the soundtrack, Gran Turismo just feels like a celebration of car culture, whereas Forza feels like a game I just can't connect with.

ğŸ”« The Xbox Shooters: Halo & Gears of War
I can hear the comments section typing already! Halo is legendary. I understand the cultural impact of Master Chief and the revolutionary multiplayer. But I just don't care about the lore, the mythos, or the Covenant.

The Alternative: Back in the day, when everyone was playing Halo, I was obsessed with a game called BLACK by Criterion (published by EA). To me, the gunplay and sound design in Black were superior.

Gears of War: This falls into the same bucket. I respect what it did for third-person cover shooters, but the world and characters never grabbed me. Being a PlayStation guy, I missed the nostalgia boat on these, and going back now? It just doesn't click.

ğŸª The Metroid Franchise
This is probably my hottest take. I know Metroid is beloved.

The NES Original: I played the original back in the day (yes, I knew the Justin Bailey code), but the lack of a map and the confusion turned me off completely.

Super Metroid: People call this the greatest game of all time. It is beautiful, and the soundtrack is amazing, but the frustration of the first game tainted the series for me. I have never finished it.

The Backlog: Fun factâ€”I actually own Metroid Prime Remastered and Metroid Dread on Switch. They are sitting right here, sealed in the box. Will I play them? Maybe someday. But honestly? Probably not anytime soon.

â›ï¸ Minecraft
My oldest daughter tried her hardest to get me into this. We sat down, booted it up, and I asked the burning question: "What do you do?" Her answer? "You build stuff." Okay... then what? "You build more stuff."

I know the game has evolved. I know there are story modes and survival elements now. But that core loop of open-ended crafting and building with no definitive direction? It never appealed to me. I need an objective, a mission, or a finish line. The "make your own fun" sandbox just isn't my style.

ğŸ•¶ï¸ ToeJam & Earl
This is a cult classic on the Sega Genesis that people hold near and dear to their hearts.

My Experience: I picked this up at MoGameCon in 2018. I was excited to see what the hype was about.

The Verdict: I played it; I streamed it; I hated it; and I sold it. The nonlinear, roguelike gameplay (before roguelikes were cool) is just too weird and "out there" for me. Itâ€™s available on the Nintendo Switch Online Sega app, but I will never boot it up again.

ğŸ—£ï¸ What Are YOUR "Anti-Favorites"?
Now that Iâ€™ve shared my gaming confessions, I want to hear yours. What is a popular game series that everyone loves, but you just can't get into? Are you a Zelda hater? Do you dislike Call of Duty? Let me know in the comments below! (And please be gentle with my Halo take!)

ğŸ® Games Mentioned
Forza Motorsport / Horizon (Xbox)

Gran Turismo (PlayStation)

Metroid / Super Metroid (NES/SNES)

Metroid Dread (Switch)

Halo: Combat Evolved (Xbox)

BLACK (PS2/Xbox)

Gears of War (Xbox)

Minecraft (Multiplatform)

ToeJam & Earl (Genesis)

Alex is a grappler character, prefering to close distance on his opponent with moves like slash elbow, and sniping enemies out of the the sky with knee smash. 

Alex comes to Street Fighter 6 on March 17 for PlayStation 5 (PS5), Xbox Series X|S, Nintendo Switch 2, and PC (Steam).

title: Welcome To Kyrat | Far Cry 4 Gameplay #1
description:
Far Cry 4 Full PC Gameplay

Far Cry 4 Walkthrough Gameplay Part 1 includes a Review and Campaign Mission 1: Border Crossing of the Single Player for PS4, Xbox One, Xbox 360, PS3 and PC. This Far Cry 4 Gameplay Walkthrough will include a Review, the Campaign Story, Main Missions, Weapons, Quests, Tiger Skills, Elephant Skills, Karma, Crafting, DLC and the Good Ending and Bad Ending.

Far Cry 4 Main Missions include: Border Crossing, Dinner with Pagan, Escape the Compound, Reach the Tower, Banapur, Hunting, Bell Towers, Banapur Attack, Hostages, Hunt or Be Hunted, Cultural Exchange, Sermon on the Mount, Reclamation, Bhadra, Guru Ashram, The Mouth of Madness, Return to Sender, The Protector's Arrival, Giant Statues, City of Pain, Advanced Chemistry, Noore's Fall, Free Willis, Death from Above, Kalinag Prison, Prison Escape, Wages of Fear, Utkarsh Town, Payback, Culture Wars, Valley of Death, Utkarsh Destroyed, Fortress, Royal Palace.

Far Cry 4 Quests include: Eye For An Eye, Assassinations, Hunting Control, Hunting Survival, Hunting Supplies, Kyrat Fashion Week, Golden Path Supplies, Hostage Rescue, Armed Escort, Bomb Defusing, Propaganda Centers, Pagan's Wrath.

Ajay Ghale is the main protagonist of Far Cry 4. Ajay travels to Kyrat to fulfill his mother's dying wish for her ashes to be spread somewhere in Kyrat. He quickly becomes involved in a brutal civil war against the oppressive andless leader of Kyrat, Pagan Min. After two choices, Ajay becomes Pagan's succesor as the King of Kyrat.
